^b@2^Y@3The first and the most critical step in Bergen's hand evaluation is counting the "Starting Points" which is the true value of each hand before the bidding. The second is "Dummy Points" which is the Starting Points of the dummy's hand after adding the dummy points after a fit. And finally the "Bergen Points" or the "Declarer Points" which is declarer's Starting Points again after a fit has been established. As this s only a brief, several portions of Bergen's hand evaluation such as "Adjust-3", the "Quality Suits",  the "Dubious Singleton/Doubletons", and etc are not discussed here. For a detailed review please check the sources mentioned above. So, let us look at what I have. Here, let me confess that in many places without shame I have copied the exact text from my sources.|
